#PressPlay: Get y’all popcorn ready, Chance the Rapper’s new movie drops today in theaters across the country! “Chance the Rapper’s Magnificent Coloring World” marks the first time an artist has independently distributed a film to theatres.
________
“Magnificent Coloring World” is a concert film self-distributed through Chance the Rapper’s House of Kicks production company and film house.
________
Chance wrote, produced, edited and starred in the film, working hard this past year to bring never-before-seen footage to his fans. The footage was filmed in 2017 right before Chance took home 3 Grammys for his critically acclaimed mixtape “Coloring Book.”
________
Fans will be able to see the film in person for a limited time in several cities including Los Angeles, New York, Chicago, Detori, Las Vegas and Philly.

node.title: Chance The Rapper’s Film Released Today

TSR Staff: Cassandra S. @__casmarie 
_______________________________
#TSRTech: #Roommates: Chile, the hackers are working hard out here — at stealing data that is! According to reports from @vice, #TMobile has launched an investigation into a forum post that’s alleging it has data belonging to more than 100 million people. 
_______________________________
Although the post didn’t name T-Mobile, the seller revealed to Vice’s Motherboard that it received the information from the telecommunications company’s servers. The personal data taken includes “social security numbers, phone numbers, names, physical addresses, unique IMEI numbers, and driver licenses information.”
_______________________________
The unknown seller is offering 30 million social security numbers and driver licenses for about $270,000, which equals out to 6 bitcoin. The remaining data is reportedly being privately sold.
_______________________________
The seller also shared that T-Mobile has since kicked them out of the hacked servers, but that the information is already downloaded and backed up. The company has said it’s aware of the data breach claims, but do not have additional information to share beyond an investigation being launched. Thoughts, #Roomies? (📸: @gettyimages)
